dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data set represents property within the New York City limits that is managed partially or solely by the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation. The data is acquired by researching current and historical property records.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data is intended to be a guide for identifying the limits of property managed partially or solely by the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation, as well as provide details about property jurisdiction, the date of acquisition, and the property type.
dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; ESRI ArcGIS 10.0.5.4400
dataIdInfo.idCredit: When used, this data set must be accompanied with a citation that references the New York City Department of Parks and Recreation and the current date.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Unique identification number for each park property, identified by borough/county (B = Brooklyn; M = Manhattan; Q = Queens; R = Richmond (Staten Island); X = Bronx) and followed by a number. New numbers are assigned sequentially to sites as they are acquired.
Unique identification number for each park property used by the Operations and Management Planning Division of the Department of Parks and Recreation for inspection purposes.
A description of the location of a property with respect to the street system and physical features such as water bodies.

edom.edomvd: Property not adjacent to water front.

attr.attrdef: Describes by the property's proximity to the water front.

attr.attrdef: Describes the status of the property on the City Map.
The name of the entire site as it appears on the signs located on the exterior of the park.
Describes the borough in which the property is located. All properties fall within a single borough.
Describes the zip code in which the property is located. If a property is located within multiple zip codes, then multiple zip codes are listed and separated by commas.
Address of the site as recorded by the New York City Department of City Planning's PLUTO database .
The name of the property as it appears in the Citywide Event Management System.
